Title: Papua New Guinea
Region: Waghi Valley, Western Highlands Province, Papua New Guinea
Process: Fully washed & Sun dried. Pulped on same day of picking, fermented for a period of three days broken down to every 24 hours of washing. Unlike other coffees, the Sigri is followed up by a total immersion of water for a further day and this creates a superior cleaner coffee.
